The course consists of lectures and seminars that are dealing with Estonia and Estonians. The courses and seminars offer several possibilities to compare Estonia and other countries. During the course, students will discover Estonia and share their personal experiences of Estonia.Objectives/eesmärkid:  The aim of the course is to introduce Estonia (state, nature, history, people and culture) to the foreign students of Tartu University. The course participations will discover similarities and differences of Estonia and their homelands and discuss their personal experiences in Estonia.Learning outcomes/õpiväljund:  During the semester the exchange student acquires preliminary knowledge of Estonia, Estonians and Estonian culture, by listening lectures, attending seminars and completing different written and oral tasks.
